### IN ORDER TO effectively ignore paths when the command is fired from a parent directory,
### the ignore patterns must be relative to the repository root, AND NOT START WITH A SLASH.
### This of course increases the risk of false positives, but it is necessary to be able to
### have clickable links in IDEs when working from ~/workspace.
###
### So, the most important paths in this file DO NOT start with a slash, but if the path is
### very short/generic, we do start with a slash to reduce false positives.
###
### For Silver Searcher, do NOT use double asterisks at the beginning of a line, as it
### treats them differently than single asterisks. Use single asterisks at the beginning
### of a line instead.

# Visual Studio Code
*/.vscode/*

# Local History for Visual Studio Code
*/.history/*

# Built Visual Studio Code Extensions
**.vsix

